  "commentary": "With SPX at 7023 sitting right at the max positive gamma strike of 7025 (37.7B), dealers are actively selling into strength to hedge their long gamma positions. The massive positive GEX wall cluster between 7000-7030 creates a strong magnetic pull that should contain price action and promote mean reversion back toward this zone on any breakout attempts. Watch for immediate resistance at 7025-7030 where dealer selling intensifies, while the 7000 level (12B GEX) provides key support as the lower bound of this high-gamma zone.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned around 7025 with limited upside momentum.",
